Your URLs After Deployment:
Frontend (Render): https://brimble-frontend.onrender.com

Backend API (Render): https://brimble-backend.onrender.com

Health Check: https://brimble-backend.onrender.com/health

Stats: https://brimble-backend.onrender.com/api/stats

Important Notes for Render Deployment:
Disk Space: Render free tier has limited disk space. SQLite will work but for production consider PostgreSQL.

Docker Socket: Render doesn't expose Docker socket, so building images inside Render won't work. You'll need to modify the pipeline or use their native build system.

Alternative: Consider using Railway or Fly.io which offer better Docker support.

Want me to help you deploy to Railway or Fly.io instead? They have better Docker and container support for this kind of pipeline! 🚀

lets add readme
Let's create a comprehensive, professional README for your project.

bash
cd ~/OneDrive/Desktop/brimble-pipeline
bash
cat > README.md << 'EOF'
# 🚀 Brimble Deployment Pipeline

[![TypeScript](https://img.shields.io/badge/TypeScript-5.3-blue.svg)](https://www.typescriptlang.org/)
[![Docker](https://img.shields.io/badge/Docker-20.10-blue.svg)](https://www.docker.com/)
[![React](https://img.shields.io/badge/React-18.2-61dafb.svg)](https://reactjs.org/)
[![Express](https://img.shields.io/badge/Express-4.18-green.svg)](https://expressjs.com/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE)

A **production-ready deployment platform** that automatically detects, builds, and deploys applications from GitHub repositories. Supports 10+ programming languages and frameworks with zero configuration.

## ✨ Features

- 🎯 **Auto-Detection** - Automatically detects project type (Node.js, Python, Go, Rust, Java, PHP, Ruby, .NET, Static sites)
- 🐳 **Docker Native** - Creates optimized Dockerfiles for each project type
- 📡 **Live Log Streaming** - Real-time build and deployment logs via SSE
- 🔄 **GitHub Webhooks** - Auto-deploy on push to main/master branch
- 📊 **Deployment Dashboard** - Modern UI with deployment history and stats
- 🗑️ **One-Click Delete** - Remove deployments with container cleanup
- 🎨 **Modern UI** - Built with React, Tailwind CSS, and Lucide icons
- 🚀 **Zero Config** - Works with most repositories out of the box

## 🛠️ Supported Technologies

| Language/Framework | Auto-Detection | Docker Image | Default Port |
|-------------------|----------------|--------------|--------------|
| **Node.js** | `package.json` | Node 20-bookworm | 3000 |
| **Python** | `requirements.txt` | Python 3.11-slim | 5000 |
| **Go** | `go.mod` | Golang 1.21-alpine | 8080 |
| **Rust** | `Cargo.toml` | Rust 1.75 | 8080 |
| **Java/Spring** | `pom.xml` / `build.gradle` | OpenJDK 17 | 8080 |
| **PHP** | `composer.json` | PHP 8.2-apache | 80 |
| **Ruby/Rails** | `Gemfile` | Ruby 3.2-slim | 3000 |
| **.NET Core** | `*.csproj` | .NET 8.0 | 5000 |
| **Static Sites** | `*.html` | Nginx Alpine | 80 |
| **Custom Docker** | `Dockerfile` | User-defined | Configurable |

## 📋 Prerequisites

- [Docker Desktop](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/) (for local development)
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) 20+ (for development)
- [Git](https://git-scm.com/) (for cloning repositories)

