🔧 API Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/api/deployments	Create new deployment
GET	/api/deployments	List all deployments
GET	/api/deployments/:id	Get deployment details
GET	/api/deployments/:id/logs	Stream live logs (SSE)
DELETE	/api/deployments/:id	Delete deployment
GET	/api/stats	Deployment statistics
GET	/health	Health check
📊 Deployment Flow
Submit Git URL → User enters repository URL and branch

Clone Repository → Backend clones the source code

Detect Project → Auto-detects language/framework

Create Dockerfile → Generates optimized Dockerfile

Build Image → Builds Docker image with dependencies

Start Container → Runs container on available port

Configure Routing → Sets up Caddy reverse proxy

Stream Logs → Real-time log streaming to UI

